---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Licensing" description="Understand the open-source and commercial licensing paths for the Signal Protocol JavaScript SDK.">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Licensing</p>
      <h1>One SDK. Two paths to production.</h1>
      <p class="lead">Use the SDK under its open-source license, or obtain commercial rights for a product that cannot meet those obligations.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container split-grid">
      <article class="split-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Open source</p>
        <h2>AGPLv3</h2>
        <p>Suitable when your distribution and network use can comply with the AGPL requirements. The repository license text—not this overview—controls.</p>
        <ul><li>Complete SDK source</li><li>No license fee</li><li>AGPL compliance required</li><li>No proprietary production grant</li></ul>
      </article>
      <article class="split-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Commercial</p>
        <h2>Named product rights</h2>
        <p>Suitable for proprietary applications that need a separately negotiated production grant without applying the AGPL to the covered product.</p>
        <ul><li>Named legal entity and product</li><li>Annual SDK update term</li><li>Startup self-service option</li><li>Growth and OEM terms available</li></ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-subtle">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div><p class="eyebrow">Important boundary</p><h2>The agreement is the license.</h2></div>
        <p>Website descriptions summarize the intended commercial model. They do not replace the executed commercial agreement or provide legal advice.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href="https://console.signal-protocol.dev/licenses/new?plan=startup">Purchase Startup</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="mailto:licensing@signal-protocol.dev?subject=Commercial%20licensing%20question">Ask a licensing question</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
